==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Up-line
<hw>Up"-line`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Railroad)</fld>
<def>A line or track leading from the provinces toward the metropolis or
a principal terminus; the track upon which up-trains run. See
<er>Up-train</er>.</def> <mark>[Eng.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Uplock</ent>⟦br⟧
